cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

This paper is about zero-shot learning in computer vision, which is a subfield of computer science that deals with image and video analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a probabilistic model, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper deals with semantic information and natural language processing, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on benchmark datasets, which could also fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
